# PART C — RLS Policies (Checklist)

## C1) `provider_applications`
- Providers can:
  - SELECT their own rows (user_id = auth.uid())
  - INSERT/UPDATE their own DRAFT/SUBMITTED rows
  - Cannot update after status becomes UNDER_REVIEW unless allowed fields (docs uploads ok)
- Admin can SELECT/UPDATE all

## C2) `provider_agreement_acceptance`
- Provider can INSERT acceptance rows only for their application
- Provider can SELECT their acceptance rows
- Admin can SELECT all

## C3) `provider_orgs`, `provider_org_members`
- Provider can SELECT/UPDATE orgs where they are a member (join on org_members)
- Admin full access

## C4) Compliance docs
- Provider can INSERT/SELECT docs for their org
- Provider cannot set VERIFIED status
- Admin can set VERIFIED/REJECTED and add notes

## C5) BYOC tables
- Provider can CREATE invite links only if org is approved
- Provider can SELECT invites/events for their org
- Customer can access `byoc/activate/:token` via token-based edge function or security-definer RPC (do NOT expose all invites)
- Admin can access all

